content: Hello dear students! We will now begin the renju lesson! Welcome!
Since ORC server does not have that rule,
therefore many people do not know about it.
As you kow, RIF is searching for new opening rule,
which could offer more playable variants,
and at the same time, the new rule should be as little change as possible from the old.
Jonsson's rule is one of the most suitable rules so far.
Let me first show you the rule itself.
and then we will discuss and analyse possible variants by that rule.
1 step: Player 1 sets an opening (just like RIF)
2 step: player 2 may swap if he wants (just like RIF)
step 3: white player will put the 4th move AND declares how many 5th will be offered in this game, 1,2 or 3.
step 4: the black player has a right to swap now
step 5: whoever is black after that, will put the named number of 5th moves on board.
now you can choose, swap or not?

there will be three 5th moves in this game!

and you can decide now, swap or not
everything else is just like current RIF rule
We are talking next rule will be like this after Yamaguchi rule in Japan.
this rule gives many playable variants,
and its very little change from RIF rule

most important different between jonsson and yamaguchi is when the number of 5th stones is the decided
the jonsson rule gives both players a chance to prepare
yamaguchi rule gives advantage to the opener
because in Yamaguchi rule SAME player decides both opening and 5th moves number
so he can have a big preparation
We think most important is not complicated for the begginers.
Jonsson rule is as simple as yamaguchi rule from the learning point
but its much fairer to players too
because one player can prepare opening,
and another player can balance by  playing his "own" 4th
